{"title":"Leap Components Print Alt AXS Shifters, Blip Buttons & Derailleur Bushing Kits","link":"https://bikerumor.com/leap-components-axs-shifter-blip-buttons-derailleur-bushing-kits/","date":1692705600000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVES-SHIFTER-PADS.jpg\" alt=\"leap components axs shifter button alternatives 3d printed carbon filled nylon\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVES-SHIFTER-PADS.jpg 1600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVES-SHIFTER-PADS-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVES-SHIFTER-PADS-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVES-SHIFTER-PADS-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVES-SHIFTER-PADS-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVES-SHIFTER-PADS-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVES-SHIFTER-PADS-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Leap Components is manufacturing some neat aftermarket alternatives for AXS Shifters, AXS Dropper Remotes, Wireless Blips and AXS Battery Mounts out of their facility in the Netherlands. All are 3D Printed from a CF15 carbon-filled Nylon, and offer riders of SRAM’s electronic drivetrains the ability to customize their cockpit with alternative looks and ergonomics. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s a quick look at the Leap Components range.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/leap-components-quickshift-axs-alternative-pads.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"667\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/leap-components-quickshift-axs-alternative-pads-800x667.jpg\" alt=\"leap components quickshift axs pad alternative ergonomics\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/leap-components-quickshift-axs-alternative-pads-800x667.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/leap-components-quickshift-axs-alternative-pads-297x247.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/leap-components-quickshift-axs-alternative-pads-120x100.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/leap-components-quickshift-axs-alternative-pads-768x640.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/leap-components-quickshift-axs-alternative-pads-1536x1280.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/leap-components-quickshift-axs-alternative-pads.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Leap Components 3D Printed Buttons for SRAM AXS</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Quickshift is Leap Components’ alternative shifter button for SRAM AXS drivetrains. In contrast to the standard SRAM GX AXS shifter, the up- and down-shift buttons have a slightly different shape. They are arranged such that they sit beside one another, rather than stacked on a single paddle. Like we see on the standard AXS option, the rear button can be actuated from the front by the rider’s thumb, or from the rear by the rider’s index finger.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Leap Components Quickshift is compatible with the AXS GX, XX1 and X01 shifters. Leap claim it offers better ergonomics and that it eliminates the “annoying play of the standard button”. The brand offer two options; without the optional spring installed, the force required to actuate a shift is around 70% of the force required to actuate a shift using the standard button. Meanwhile, with the spring installed, the force requirement is the same.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Leap’s 3D printed alternative to SRAM AXS shifter buttons retails at €28.93. You can custom engrave the part with text or a logo for an extra €4. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-QUICKSHIFT-ALTERNATIVE-SRAM-AXS-CONTROLLER-BUTTONS.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-QUICKSHIFT-ALTERNATIVE-SRAM-AXS-CONTROLLER-BUTTONS-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"leap components quickshift alternative axs button remote pad\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-QUICKSHIFT-ALTERNATIVE-SRAM-AXS-CONTROLLER-BUTTONS-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-QUICKSHIFT-ALTERNATIVE-SRAM-AXS-CONTROLLER-BUTTONS-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-QUICKSHIFT-ALTERNATIVE-SRAM-AXS-CONTROLLER-BUTTONS-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-QUICKSHIFT-ALTERNATIVE-SRAM-AXS-CONTROLLER-BUTTONS-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-QUICKSHIFT-ALTERNATIVE-SRAM-AXS-CONTROLLER-BUTTONS-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-QUICKSHIFT-ALTERNATIVE-SRAM-AXS-CONTROLLER-BUTTONS.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Leap Components offer something similar for the SRAM AXS Dropper Remote – the Quickshift Seatshift. It too can be installed with or without the spring for a customized actuation feel. Pick it up for €14.88.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVES-SHIFTER-PADS.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVES-SHIFTER-PADS-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"leap components axs shifter button alternatives 3d printed carbon filled nylon\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVES-SHIFTER-PADS-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVES-SHIFTER-PADS-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVES-SHIFTER-PADS-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVES-SHIFTER-PADS-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVES-SHIFTER-PADS-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVES-SHIFTER-PADS-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVES-SHIFTER-PADS.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>You can also purchase Quickshift and Seatshift buttons as a combo for €41.32</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Leap Components Wireless Blip Alternatives</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>There’s 3D printed alternatives for the SRAM Wireless Blips, too. They have on-bar mounts; one for accomodating a single Blip, and another for accomodating two Blips. The mounts are available in 22.2 mm for MTB bars and 23.6 mm for gravel bars. A pair of single mounts and buttons retails at €23.14 for the single mount option. The Blipshift Mount with two buttons installed retails at the same price.</p>\n\n\n\n<div><div><div><div><figure><img srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-BLIP-SHIFTER-ALTERNATIVE-PAD-BUTTON-800x534.jpg?strip=info&amp;w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-BLIP-SHIFTER-ALTERNATIVE-PAD-BUTTON-800x534.jpg?strip=info&amp;w=900&amp;ssl=1 900w, https://i0.wp.com/bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-BLIP-SHIFTER-ALTERNATIVE-PAD-BUTTON-800x534.jpg?strip=info&amp;w=1200&amp;ssl=1 1200w, https://i0.wp.com/bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-BLIP-SHIFTER-ALTERNATIVE-PAD-BUTTON-800x534.jpg?strip=info&amp;w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i0.wp.com/bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-BLIP-SHIFTER-ALTERNATIVE-PAD-BUTTON-800x534.jpg?strip=info&amp;w=1600&amp;ssl=1 1600w\" alt=\"wireless blip mounts leap components on-bar double\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-BLIP-SHIFTER-ALTERNATIVE-PAD-BUTTON-800x534.jpg?ssl=1\" /></figure></div><div><figure><img srcset=\"https://i1.wp.com/bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/WIRLESS-BLI-MOUNT-LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-SHIFTER-ALTERNATIVE-PADS-800x534.jpg?strip=info&amp;w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i1.wp.com/bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/WIRLESS-BLI-MOUNT-LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-SHIFTER-ALTERNATIVE-PADS-800x534.jpg?strip=info&amp;w=900&amp;ssl=1 900w, https://i1.wp.com/bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/WIRLESS-BLI-MOUNT-LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-SHIFTER-ALTERNATIVE-PADS-800x534.jpg?strip=info&amp;w=1200&amp;ssl=1 1200w, https://i1.wp.com/bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/WIRLESS-BLI-MOUNT-LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-SHIFTER-ALTERNATIVE-PADS-800x534.jpg?strip=info&amp;w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i1.wp.com/bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/WIRLESS-BLI-MOUNT-LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-SHIFTER-ALTERNATIVE-PADS-800x534.jpg?strip=info&amp;w=1600&amp;ssl=1 1600w\" alt=\"wireless blip mounts leap components on-bar single\" src=\"https://i1.wp.com/bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/WIRLESS-BLI-MOUNT-LEAP-COMPONENTS-AXS-SHIFTER-ALTERNATIVE-PADS-800x534.jpg?ssl=1\" /></figure></div></div></div></div>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/SRAM-WIRELESS-BLIP-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVE-LEAP-COMPONENTS.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"334\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/SRAM-WIRELESS-BLIP-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVE-LEAP-COMPONENTS-800x334.jpg\" alt=\"wireless blip button alternative leap components\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/SRAM-WIRELESS-BLIP-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVE-LEAP-COMPONENTS-800x334.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/SRAM-WIRELESS-BLIP-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVE-LEAP-COMPONENTS-297x124.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/SRAM-WIRELESS-BLIP-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVE-LEAP-COMPONENTS-120x50.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/SRAM-WIRELESS-BLIP-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVE-LEAP-COMPONENTS-768x320.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/SRAM-WIRELESS-BLIP-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVE-LEAP-COMPONENTS-1536x640.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/SRAM-WIRELESS-BLIP-CONTROL-ALTERNATIVE-LEAP-COMPONENTS.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>SRAM AXS Wireless Blip Shifter with standard button (left), and Leap Components’ aftermarket alternative (right)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Leap Components also produce a Wireless Blip Mount for TT bars, too. This is available in a standard option, or a 45 degree option, allowing riders to customize the ergonomics to their liking. A pair will set you back €25.62.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-SRAM-AXS-BATTERY-MOUNT-LATERNATIVE-LEAP-COMPONENTS-TT-WIRELESS-BLIP-BUTTONS.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"261\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-SRAM-AXS-BATTERY-MOUNT-LATERNATIVE-LEAP-COMPONENTS-TT-WIRELESS-BLIP-BUTTONS-800x261.jpg\" alt=\"leap components wireless blip button mount alternatives tt bars axs battery mount\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-SRAM-AXS-BATTERY-MOUNT-LATERNATIVE-LEAP-COMPONENTS-TT-WIRELESS-BLIP-BUTTONS-800x261.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-SRAM-AXS-BATTERY-MOUNT-LATERNATIVE-LEAP-COMPONENTS-TT-WIRELESS-BLIP-BUTTONS-297x97.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-SRAM-AXS-BATTERY-MOUNT-LATERNATIVE-LEAP-COMPONENTS-TT-WIRELESS-BLIP-BUTTONS-120x39.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-SRAM-AXS-BATTERY-MOUNT-LATERNATIVE-LEAP-COMPONENTS-TT-WIRELESS-BLIP-BUTTONS-768x251.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-SRAM-AXS-BATTERY-MOUNT-LATERNATIVE-LEAP-COMPONENTS-TT-WIRELESS-BLIP-BUTTONS-1536x501.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/LEAP-COMPONENTS-SRAM-AXS-BATTERY-MOUNT-LATERNATIVE-LEAP-COMPONENTS-TT-WIRELESS-BLIP-BUTTONS.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4>More Neat Solutions from Leap Components</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Leap also offer a neat solution for storing a spare AXS battery underneath the saddle. The mount fits all standard 7mm rails. Furthermore, it has an integrated valve core removal tool, and space to accomodate a spare SRAM Powerlink. Leap say it forms a watertight seal with the battery, and on the rear there is a little slider that the rider can use to remind themselves of the battery’s status; charged or empty. And, there’s an optional IP64 watertight Airtag holder to go with it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Of course, it doesn’t actually fit onto RockShox Reverb AXS dropper seat posts. Leap sell the SRAM AXS Battery Saddle Mount for €18.18, without the AirTag, chain link, or PH1 bit required to install it. Get those at an additional cost.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/GARMIN-MOUNT-LEAP-COMPONENTS-3D-PRINTED.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"395\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/GARMIN-MOUNT-LEAP-COMPONENTS-3D-PRINTED-800x395.jpg\" alt=\"leap components garmin mount\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/GARMIN-MOUNT-LEAP-COMPONENTS-3D-PRINTED-800x395.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/GARMIN-MOUNT-LEAP-COMPONENTS-3D-PRINTED-297x146.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/GARMIN-MOUNT-LEAP-COMPONENTS-3D-PRINTED-120x59.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/GARMIN-MOUNT-LEAP-COMPONENTS-3D-PRINTED-768x379.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/GARMIN-MOUNT-LEAP-COMPONENTS-3D-PRINTED-1536x757.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/GARMIN-MOUNT-LEAP-COMPONENTS-3D-PRINTED.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>There’s a Leap Components Garmin and Wahoo click-in frame mount, too, available in 10 sizes.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Also of note is the SRAM AXS Derailleur bushing repair kit for GX, X01 and XX1, a very nice addition that will help riders prolong the usable lifetime of their expensive electronic drivetrain. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Five bushing sets, a replacement rod, with the mounting bolt and retainer rings, spring tool and 3.9 mm drill bit will set you back €73.55. That said, you don’t have to buy all of the above; Leap sell each of these items independently, with the five bushing sets alone costing €47.93.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And, there’s more to come. Leap is working on alternatives for the GX and X01/XX1 pod shifters, stating they believe they can make them much better. They are also teasing a shifter with integrated dropper seat post. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://leapcomponents.com/\" target=\"_blank\">leapcomponents.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/leap-components-axs-shifter-blip-buttons-derailleur-bushing-kits/\">Leap Components Print Alt AXS Shifters, Blip Buttons &amp; Derailleur Bushing Kits</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"06971c2e6d6098bd58c69a099a053311688e02afb6ee11e3f2d70be2e57b86b3","category":"Cycling"}